@startuml Mode2_OTP_AssumeRole_EC2_EN
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #0f1117
skinparam defaultFontColor #e0e0e0
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #4fc3f7
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #4fc3f7

skinparam SequenceDividerBackgroundColor #1565c0
skinparam SequenceDividerBorderColor #4fc3f7
skinparam SequenceDividerFontColor #ffffff
skinparam SequenceDividerFontSize 13
skinparam SequenceDividerFontStyle bold

skinparam participantBackgroundColor #1e3a5f
skinparam participantBorderColor #4fc3f7
skinparam participantFontColor #e0e0e0

skinparam actorBackgroundColor #1e3a5f
skinparam actorBorderColor #4fc3f7
skinparam actorFontColor #e0e0e0

skinparam noteBackgroundColor #12263a
skinparam noteBorderColor #1565c0
skinparam noteFontColor #b3e5fc

title Mode2 NML Ops Chatbot — OTP / AssumeRole / EC2 Operation

actor "User\n(Browser)" as User
participant "ECS / Fargate\n[mode2-ecs-task-role]" as ECS
participant "Lambda\nOTP Function\n[mode2-lambda-otp-role]" as Lambda
participant "DynamoDB\nChatBot-OTP-Verification" as DDB
participant "SES\nEmail Service" as SES
participant "STS\nAssumeRole" as STS
participant "Target Account\nmode2-ops-role" as TargetRole
participant "EC2 / RDS\n(mode2-managed=true)" as EC2

== ④ OTP Two-Factor Authentication (Required before EC2 operations) ==

note over ECS, Lambda
  🔐 All EC2/RDS operations require OTP verification
  This acts as a safety mechanism against accidental or unauthorized changes
end note

ECS -> Lambda : Request OTP generation\n(user email, operation type)
Lambda -> Lambda : Generate 6-digit OTP randomly
Lambda -> DDB : Store OTP temporarily\n(TTL: 10 min, status: pending)

note right of Lambda
  ⚠️ Must remove before production release:
  print(f"Generated OTP: {otp_code}")
  ↑ OTP is exposed in logs — security risk
end note

Lambda -> SES : Send OTP email\nFrom: no-reply-security@mail.nissan.co.jp
SES --> User : 📧 OTP email delivered

User -> ECS : Enter and submit OTP code
ECS -> Lambda : OTP validation request
Lambda -> DDB : Verify OTP\n(check expiry + used flag)
DDB --> Lambda : Verification result
Lambda --> ECS : ✅ OTP verified — operation permitted

== ⑤ Cross-Account Access via STS AssumeRole ==

note over ECS, STS
  🔑 ECS cannot operate EC2 directly
  ECS borrows temporary credentials via STS to perform operations
end note

ECS -> STS : AssumeRole request\nTarget role: mode2-ops-role\nShared secret (ExternalId): mode2-chatbot-trusted

note right of STS
  Supported target accounts:
  - B2C       NonProd / Prod
  - Internal  NonProd / Prod
  - Gamma     NonProd / Prod
  * Access denied if ExternalId does not match
end note

STS -> TargetRole : Validate Trust Policy\n(Verify Principal + ExternalId)
TargetRole --> STS : Trust policy validated
STS --> ECS : Issue temporary credentials\n(Valid for 15 min – 1 hour)

== ⑥ EC2 / RDS Operation Execution and Notification ==

note over ECS, EC2
  🏷️ Only instances tagged with "mode2-managed = true"
  can be operated. Untagged instances are blocked.
end note

ECS -> EC2 : Execute EC2/RDS operation\n(Start / Stop / Reboot / Describe)

note right of EC2
  IAM Condition key:
  ec2:ResourceTag/mode2-managed = true
  → Untagged instances are denied at IAM level
end note

EC2 --> ECS : Return operation result
ECS -> SES : Send completion notification\n(to operator + team)
SES --> User : ✅ Operation complete email received
ECS --> User : Display result in browser

@enduml
